Sentencas: Sample of nominal composition La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3 (LCFN) was prepared by liquid mix method.
Titulo: Optimization of La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The structure of the polycrystalline powder was analyzed with X-ray powder diffraction data.
Titulo: Optimization of La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This compound shows orthorhombic perovskite structure with a space group Pnma.
Titulo: Optimization of La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In order to improve the electrochemical performance, Sm-doped ceria (SDC) powder was added to prepare the LCFN-SDC composite cathodes.
Titulo: Optimization of La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical characteristics of the composites have been investigated for possible application as cathode material for an intermediate-temperature-operating solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Optimization of La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance was studied using Sm-doped ceria (SDC).
Titulo: Optimization of La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy measurements of LCFN-SDC/SDC/LCFN-SDC test cell were carried out.
Titulo: Optimization of La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These electrochemical experiments were performed at equilibrium from 850 degrees C to room temperature, under both zero dc current intensity and air.
Titulo: Optimization of La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The best value of area-specific resistance (ASR) was for LCFN cathode doped with 10% of SDC (LCFN-SDC9010), 0.13 Omega cm(2) at 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Optimization of La0.6Ca0.4Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The dc four-probe measurement exhibits a total electrical conductivity over 100 S cm(-1) at T >= 600 degrees C for LCFN-SDC9010 composite cathode.
